<br>
However, if you happen to have amazing TG accessories, and all MP armor/weapons, and you can put 5 pt overcharges on them, etc, etc., so you really can put in fluff...<br>
<br>
...put in +battlesongs.  You would get about +1 damage per DD per point of Battlesongs, and if you decide to spec Battlesongs below the usual 46, you would get some small benefit from variance.  So maybe you can do some more damage, albeit a small amount more.<br>
<br>
+power is really of no value.  It's possible after a long series of fights that you might be able to get off 1 more DD or mez, that's all. <p>Clapperoth Liefarg<br>
Guild Officer<br>
Rune<br>
