<br>
What would you go for? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=clapperoth>Clapperoth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 101<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/5/03 6:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=76.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ok, so what...</span><hr size=1> Dexterity.  Parry is based solely off of Dex, and Dex is a modifier in your &quot;to hit&quot; factor (i.e. it's worked into the equation that decides if you will hit an opponent or not).<br>
<br>
Some skalds go with quickness instead, wanting to speed up their 2h weapon which has a small increase in their damage over time as another option.  In my opinion, Dex is more valuable but some have argued with me. <p>Clapperoth Liefarg<br>
Guild Officer<br>
